review_body: This is crazy. For no reason at all the app won't detect the SD card, which is where the camera's folder is located. When I went to Settings to try to sort it out, I noticed the Dark Mode switch was off. It's always been on Dark since I set it ages ago when I first installed. When I went to Settings to try to sort it out, I noticed the Dark Mode switch was off. It's always been on Dark since I set it ages ago when I first installed. It's still on Dark now but the switch isn't. I don't auto update so I'd know if it was an update that screwed this up. I don't recall updating the app so I assume it just decided to misbehave.

I use this app in conjunction with Google Photos and I find myself using Gallery Go more often than the full fledged Photos app, simply because Gallery Go displays photos and videos stored locally on your device rather than a combination of cloud and local media storage. Google Photos is the ultimat...Full ReviewI use this app in conjunction with Google Photos and I find myself using Gallery Go more often than the full fledged Photos app, simply because Gallery Go displays photos and videos stored locally on your device rather than a combination of cloud and local media storage. Google Photos is the ultimate Photo app, but the simple interface of Gallery Go coupled with the app showing only the stuff you currently have on device makes this a valuable media manager.
